# A row-polymorphic accessor exported across the module boundary: `id-of` reads
# an `id` field off *any* record, whatever its other fields. The exported type is
# `fun {id: a, ..} -> string` -- an open record. `main` applies it to two different
# record shapes, which only type-checks if each use site instantiates a *fresh* row
# variable (the import must not pin the tail to the first call's shape).
public def id-of = fun r {
	to-string r.id
}
